Description: Fragment of wall of Attic black-figured pottery open vase, perhaps a krater. Inside glazed. Outside, upper part of female - 'penguin woman' - to right, probably following another, of which a minimal part is preserved; red for hair and hem of chiton.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2199)
